$interpreted: Tingko: Jiyanama, is the princess feeling any better?
Jiyanama: She still has a bit of a fever, but she's doing much better.
Tindoiimu: Please don't worry, I'm fine.
Jiyanama: How could you say you're fine!? You can't even stand! ...Or are you just excited for Jihasaha's arrival?
Jiyanama: I know you two love to chit-chat, but I'm afraid you'll get withering sickness. Your qi is still too weak.
Jiyanama: The doctor says it's nothing too serious right now, but that it could get worse if you don't rest.
Jiyanama: Tingko, you should go get Jihasaha's letter today. Let him know the princess won't be able to see him.
Jiyanama: What's wrong?
Tingko: Sorry, Jiyanama... But, did you just say I have to go see Jihasaha this time?
Jiyanama: I have to stay here and take care of the princess, so that leaves you to go get the letter. Princess, is it okay with you if Tingko goes?
Tindoiimu: It's fine... Thank you, Tingko.
Tingko: Yes... but...
Jiyanama: The princess said she's okay with it, so what are you waiting for?
Tingko: But, Jiyanama... you know, it's Jihasaha...
Jiyanama: And what does that matter!? Our duty is to serve the princess!
Tingko: Princess... what should I tell him?
Tindoiimu: ...Just tell him it was my idea. You're doing me a favor.

Tingko: Okay... Thank you, princess. 
Then, I will try to relax...
Tingko: (Ugh... But how could I relax? Even telling him I was sent by the princess... will he even listen to me?)
Tingko: (Thinking back to what those guards used to call him... that name...)
New Guard: The "Royal Horn"?
Lazy Guard: Yeah. The guy grew up on the streets, fighting and stealing and all that. Whatever kind of bad stuff you can think of.
New Guard: Yeah but that's no surprise, right? The insects are a bunch of scum.
Lazy Guard: Well, imagine one of those bugs beating up ten fully-grown adults when he's still just a kid.
Lazy Guard: Scary, huh? And that's just when he was young. Then he joined the military and was constantly at odds with his commanders.
New Guard: Hmph... then what got him the cool nickname?
Lazy Guard: That's how the Insect Tribe gets the strong ones to stick around, I guess.
Lazy Guard: Anyway, you'll have your chance to go over to their parts soon enough. Then you'll really get a sense of how savage they can be...
Tingko: The princess says those are all rumors, but... those things I saw...
Tingko: Hmm... why is it that so many of those rebellious types end up joining the military?
Drunk Guard: Eh... *hic*~ that... uh... I remember you. Yer that... somebody's slave girl or somethin'...
Drunk Guard: Can't you do some... some shiny *hic* light trick? Come on, let me see~
Tingko: I'm sorry, sir, I should really be going...
Drunk Guard: What? Don't you understand... *hic* respect!?
Tingko: I'm sorry, I don't mean to be disrespectful... I just really have something to do...
Drunk Guard: Something to... You got your stupid head and your... *hic* stupid brain... What the hell could... could you have to do!?
Tingko: I...
Drunk Guard: Who would... would trust YOU to do anything!? Yer bug-brain master got a... *hic* a screw loose?
Tingko: Shut up! Say what you want about me, but don't you insult the princess!
Drunk Guard: You little...!
Drunk Guard: Who's there!? Can't you see I'm busy over here!?
Jihasaha: Where's the princess?
